review_blob: Quite the bang for your buck at 8.1% alcohol. Metallic, light beer tasting with absolutely no body. Gotta be fortified, anything lacking this much body has to be fortified, which leads to another problem - expect a very raw and angry drunk from this poison. 211 is one digit from the number that will be called on you later on: 911. If you can drink 3 or more of these and not be tazored and/or arrested, your 3rd can was probably not a 211, but a Tilt.

At $1.25 for 24 ounces of pure alcohol pleasure,  Hurricane is the best buy on the market.  Hurricane stands alone among the 8.1% alcohol beers, as it clobbers the thick - never -seeming -cold enough Old English HG, and smoothly beats  the sure fire 911 call that accompanies 211 Steel Reserve.
Anheuser Busch again proves why they are the king of beers.

Mark D, Seattle
